<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<Defs>

	<ThingDef ParentName="CGF1_MWP_AssaultRifle_Carbine_T1">
		<defName>CGF1_MWP_Khyber_AKMSU_Boarder_</defName>
		<label>Khyber AKMSU "Boarder"</label>
		<description>Caliber: 7.62x39mm. 30-round detachable mag. Select-Fire.
		
This is a Khyber Pass-produced AK carbine similar to the Soviet AKS-74U, but chambered in 7.62x39mm instead of 5.45x39mm. The name "AKMSU" itself is something of a misnomer, as it originally refered to a specific carbine rifle that was mistakenly believed by western sources to be a 7.62 variant of the AKS-74U used by the USSR during its War in Afghanistan. In reality, no such carbines were ever made in the USSR and the weapon was actually a more modern production rifle built off of a Chinese Type 56, just like this example.</description>
